.so man.macros
.TH runtimeError 3 1.0 Jacl "Jacl Library Procedures"
.BS
.SH CLASS
tcl.lang.TclRuntimeError -- This class is used to report an unrecoverable errors.

.SH CONSTRUCTORS
.sp
\fBTclRuntimeError\fR(String \fIerrMsg\fR)

.SH ARGUMENTS
.AS String errMsg .
.AP String errMsg
Error message to print out.
.BE

.SH DESCRIPTION
.TP
\fBTclRuntimeError\fR
TclRuntimeError is used to report an unrecoverable error inside any
Java code that implements the Tcl interpreter or extensions. When a
TclRuntimeError is thrown, it stops Tcl execution immediately and
prints out the error message, \fIerrMsg\fR.

.SH "EQUIVALENT C FUNCTIONS"
panic

.SH "SEE ALSO"
Interp, TclException

